# Changelog

## [2.0.0] - 2026-04-28

### Added

- Added local LDAP development stack support with seeded test users.
- Added `npm run seed:ldap` to populate the local LDAP directory.
- Added LDAP test users: `alice`, `karim`, `sophie`, `thomas`, `nadia`, `ldap.user`.
- Added support for LDAP `uid` authentication fallback in addition to `sAMAccountName`.
- Added automatic creation of local external users after successful LDAP authentication.
- Added one-click LDAP user import from the admin LDAP configuration screen.
- Added `POST /api/ldap/import-users` to import LDAP users into the local database.
- Added mail rendering and delivery tests.
- Added `npm run test:mail:send` to send all mail templates to a mail catcher.
- Added `mailparser` test tooling for MIME compatibility checks.
- Added daily notification deduplication with `EmailNotificationLog`.
- Added anti-spam protection for delayed-return and reservation-code emails.
- Added reservation mode helpers and tests for automatic, click-based, and code-based flows.
- Added automatic visual status handling for `FLUENT` reservations.
- Added improved reservation stepper active-state handling.
- Added shared API security helpers: `requireAuth`, `requireAdmin`, role checks, ownership checks, and in-memory rate limiting.
- Added MySQL migration coverage for configuration tables and schema fields that previously existed only in Prisma schema/client expectations.
- Added production environment validation for `NEXTAUTH_URL` and `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_ENDPOINT`.
- Added service-secret support for cron-triggered email sends via `CRON_SECRET`.
- Added distinct production seed behavior for admin/resource-type initialization and richer demo data generation.

### Changed

- Updated LDAP configuration flow to support local Docker LDAP and Keycloak-style LDAP mappings.
- Updated reservation list status logic:
  - `FLUENT` reservations become visually `En cours` during their booking window.
  - `FLUENT` reservations become visually `Terminé` after their end date.
- Updated reservation detail stepper:
  - Step 3 is active only while the reservation is in progress.
  - Step 4 is active/validated when the reservation is returned or automatically ended.
- Updated delayed-return warning email wording to clarify that another user is waiting for the resource.
- Reworked email generation to produce safer HTML-only `7bit` messages for problematic mail clients.
- Removed CID image usage from emails to avoid broken multipart rendering in some clients.
- Normalized email subjects to ASCII-safe headers.
- Hardened email templates against `undefined` and `[object Object]` output.
- Moved repeated delayed-return reminders to scheduler-compatible daily deduplication logic.
- Updated delayed reminder scheduling to avoid repeated spam for the same reservation during a single day.
- Restricted API middleware behavior so `/api` is no longer globally public.
- Changed unauthenticated API responses from HTML redirects to JSON `401` responses.
- Restricted CORS handling to trusted origins instead of reflecting arbitrary request origins.
- Aligned the local Docker database stack with production MySQL.
- Switched Vercel installs to `npm ci` for reproducible releases.
- Changed SSO login to validate the Kerberos ticket server-side instead of trusting a client-provided username.

### Fixed

- Fixed LDAP authentication when the LDAP username attribute is `uid`.
- Fixed local LDAP test user import and verification workflow.
- Fixed broken email rendering where MIME boundaries and quoted-printable content appeared in the message body.
- Fixed broken accents in received emails such as `r=C3=A9servation`.
- Fixed `[object Object]` appearing in email templates when resources/domains were passed as objects.
- Fixed `undefined` appearing in email templates when optional fields were missing.
- Fixed duplicate delayed-return and reservation-code emails being sent multiple times per day.
- Fixed mail smoke tests failing in Jest/jsdom due to missing `setImmediate`.
- Fixed reservation status display for automatic/no-protection resources.
- Fixed stepper color behavior for active reservation steps.
- Fixed reservation IDOR risks by restricting standard users to their own reservations.
- Fixed MySQL seed failures caused by missing `pickable`, `entry`, LDAP, SMTP, Kerberos, and schedule-option schema fields in historical migrations.
- Fixed resource notification email endpoints using the wrong Nodemailer transport factory.
- Fixed production seed script path and prevented creation of the default `admin/admin` account in production.
- Fixed production seed safety by requiring explicit admin seed credentials from environment variables.
- Fixed cron email calls failing against authenticated mail endpoints when `CRON_SECRET` is configured.

### Security

- Added server-side validation for mail send payloads.
- Added daily uniqueness guard for sensitive notification emails.
- Imported LDAP users are created as external users with no local password.
- Protected sensitive API endpoints with authentication and admin role checks.
- Locked down SMTP, LDAP, SSO, users, upload, logs, mail, authorized-location, and resource-notification endpoints.
- Added rate limiting to login, registration, mail sending, and SMTP/mail test endpoints.
- Disabled public Kerberos configuration exposure.
- Disabled test Kerberos tickets in production.
- Removed password hashes and internal fields from SSO/auth user responses and session token merges.
- Reduced sensitive data returned by authorization-location checks.
- Reduced detailed error responses from sensitive endpoints outside development.
- Audited npm dependencies, upgraded vulnerable direct dependencies, removed unused vulnerable packages, and eliminated critical/high audit findings.

### Tests

- Added LDAP normalization tests.
- Added reservation mode tests.
- Added mail MIME/rendering tests.
- Added mail template smoke sending test for all templates.
- Added API authorization, CORS, and rate-limit tests.
- Validated with:
  - `npx prisma migrate status`
  - `npx prisma migrate deploy`
  - `npm run seed`
  - `npm run seed:demo`
  - `npm run lint`
  - `npm test -- --runInBand`
  - `npm run build`
  - `npm run test:mail:send`
